1
00:01:05,690 --> 00:01:08,276
I had no motive to poison Basil.

2
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,861
I loved my husband.

3
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:14,074
If you think about it,
you had a bigger motive than me.

4
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:15,992
What did you say?!

5
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:18,828
<i>Mother, they don't want me</i>
<i>near my husband,</i>

6
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:21,873
and now I'm even a suspect in his death!

7
00:01:21,956 --> 00:01:24,000
Both of you are to blame!

8
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:27,086
We need to get your fingerprints
for our investigation.

9
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:28,838
- Is that okay?
- Jerico, are you okay?

10
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:31,424
<i>Ever since the party,</i>
<i>you've been restless.</i>

11
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:34,427
You're always looking for something.
You're always worried.

12
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:35,929
- What's the problem?
- Nothing!

13
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:37,180
Why do you keep pressing me?!

14
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:41,267
I told you a thousand times,
don't call me your sister.

15
00:01:41,351 --> 00:01:44,854
Even if we count our wrinkles,
you will win.

16
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:46,189
For a dead loved one.

17
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:48,233
For a dead loved one, justice to be done.

18
00:01:48,316 --> 00:01:49,692
Justice to be done…

19
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:52,987
PREVIOUSLY

20
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:55,281
<i>Why are you crying over him, Aurora?</i>

21
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:58,034
He's my nephew, Amando.

22
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:01,329
He wanted to steal Paco's place
in the company.

23
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:02,747
It's a good thing that he is gone.

24
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:05,458
<i>He would have stolen your position too.</i>

25
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:15,885
Hey!

26
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:18,304
Sir, they just asked me
to bring them here.

27
00:02:18,388 --> 00:02:19,764
I'm being careful.

28
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,266
Very, very careful.

29
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:22,809
Wow, Louie.

30
00:02:22,892 --> 00:02:24,144
It seems like only a little while ago

31
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:26,437
that the murder of
your Grandfather Gustavo and Auntie Diana

32
00:02:26,521 --> 00:02:28,064
was the hot topic.

33
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:32,694
I heard about Mr. Paco.

34
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:34,863
Didn't his wife become a suspect?

35
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:39,284
And now, it's Mr. Basil's wife
who is the suspect.

36
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:41,244
- My sister is not the killer!
- Ward!

37
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,871
Chill, it's fine.

38
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:44,247
Chill! Sorry!

39
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:48,543
So, shall we start?

40
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:50,712
Spirits…

41
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,798
Spirits…

42
00:02:54,674 --> 00:02:56,050
Spirits, O hear us.

43
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:57,635
Hear us, O spirits.

44
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,387
Please tell us,

45
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:01,222
who poisoned Basil?

46
00:03:05,101 --> 00:03:06,686
Do you guys really believe in this stuff?

47
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:15,570
Spirits!

48
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:17,739
Hear us!

49
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:20,533
Hear us, O spirits!

50
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,410
Please!

51
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,538
Who poisoned Basil?

52
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:39,886
L…

53
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,014
O…

54
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:43,932
O.

55
00:03:46,809 --> 00:03:47,769
U…

56
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,563
I…

57
00:03:58,821 --> 00:03:59,781
E…

58
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:01,574
- Louie?
- Louie?

59
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:03,534
What's that?

60
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:39,737
So you're a killer!

61
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:41,406
Ward!

62
00:04:41,489 --> 00:04:42,657
Did you do that on purpose?

63
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:44,742
Did you move the planchette?

64
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:45,952
Yes.

65
00:04:46,035 --> 00:04:48,871
This killer is not taking this seriously.

66
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:50,873
I am not a killer!

67
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,292
- Hey, Louie! Louie, no!
- Hey! Hey!

68
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,377
- Ward! Louie! That's enough!
- Hey, stop it!

69
00:04:56,212 --> 00:04:57,505
I…

70
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,304
I sense a presence.

71
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,310
Is that you, Basil?

72
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,229
Basil?

73
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:16,649
Basil?

74
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:21,112
Are you the one with us now?

75
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,197
Please,

76
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,074
tell me,

77
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:28,077
who poisoned you?

78
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:31,497
Who poisoned you, Basil?

79
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:06,449
The spirits won't tell me,

80
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:08,534
but…

81
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:11,245
I received a message.

82
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,336
Everyone will soon…

83
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:21,798
find out…

84
00:06:23,007 --> 00:06:25,551
who poisoned Basil.

85
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,835
I will just encode this.

86
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:00,545
Okay.

87
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:04,215
Sir, where is Sarge Abdul?

88
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:05,883
- Dude.
- Sir.

89
00:07:08,177 --> 00:07:11,472
I didn't tell anyone
about my relationship with George,

90
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,474
so can we just get back to work?

91
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:14,517
Over here, sir.

92
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:21,524
Sir!

93
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:23,151
Sir, someone is looking for you.

94
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:24,527
Thank you.

95
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,611
Sir, Sarge.

96
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:27,488
What is it?

97
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,991
I know something that might possibly
help with Sir Basil's case.

98
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:31,951
What's that?

99
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:35,121
Sir, I was not the only one
who fought with him.

100
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:37,123
He also fought with someone
during the party.

101
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:40,543
I witnessed that and it was
also caught on CCTV.

102
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:07,195
Sir, this came from the crime lab.

103
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,947
It's the fingerprint match results
for Mr. Palacios' case.

104
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,032
Thank you.

105
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,925
So the other set of fingerprints
on Mr. Palacios' glass are his?

106
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:35,598
We have our primary suspect, Villa.

107
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,566
- Is that complete?
- Yes.

108
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:56,577
Thanks. You can go.

109
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,058
Amando,

110
00:09:20,184 --> 00:09:24,063
I was up the whole night thinking about
what you said at the wake.

111
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:26,440
Which thing?

112
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,859
We talked about a lot of things.

113
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:32,863
Why are you crying over him, Aurora?

114
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:34,448
You're just wasting your tears.

115
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:36,534
He's my nephew, Amando.

116
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:37,952
Who had no respect for you,

117
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:40,580
and who wanted to steal Paco's place
in the company.

118
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:42,206
It's a good thing that he is gone.

119
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:44,667
He would have stolen your position too.

120
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:48,588
It's about Basil.

121
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:51,924
When Paco died,

122
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:54,260
I saw you grieve.

123
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:57,930
But when Basil died, I saw nothing.

124
00:10:01,058 --> 00:10:04,228
I loved Paco. He was like a son to me.

125
00:10:04,312 --> 00:10:06,063
I know, Amando.

126
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,692
But you're not so mad at Basil

127
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:13,362
that you should be happy when he died.

128
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,618
Unless…

129
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:20,453
Unless what?

130
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:26,250
I remember the last time I got drunk.

131
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:34,175
Paco would not commit suicide!

132
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:36,969
My son wouldn't do that.

133
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:40,765
Aurora…

134
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:44,894
No, my son would not do that Amando!

135
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:47,229
He was killed! Paco was killed!

136
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,357
Aurora, that's enough.

137
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:53,944
If it wasn't Sam who killed my son,
then someone else did!

138
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:55,696
Someone else did!

139
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:58,240
Someone else did!

140
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:00,242
Who could it be?

141
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:07,083
Who else wants to steal Paco's position
in the company and in our family?

142
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,251
Who?

143
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:12,755
Basil.

144
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:15,299
Who else?

145
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:21,680
If I could kill them, Amando,
I would do it.

146
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:25,601
I will kill my son's killer!

147
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:43,160
Tell me honestly, Amando.

148
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:45,788
Tell me the truth.

149
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,625
Did you poison Basil?

150
00:11:55,172 --> 00:11:56,549
Did you kill him?

151
00:11:58,509 --> 00:11:59,802
For me?

152
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,148
Amando,

153
00:12:13,107 --> 00:12:14,275
I need to know.

154
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:18,112
Did you poison Basil

155
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:20,573
for me?

156
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:24,743
- Francis, son.
- Mother!

157
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:27,163
- Where are we going?
- Sam!

158
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:30,124
Mother, we're just going for a stroll
for some family bonding. Let's go.

159
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:39,216
Sam, let's go.

160
00:12:40,176 --> 00:12:41,177
Sam!

161
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:44,430
Sam!

162
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:47,600
Why are you running?

163
00:12:47,975 --> 00:12:50,019
Are you not thinking about my grandchild?

164
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:52,521
And you, Mercy?

165
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:54,023
You should know better!

166
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:55,274
No, Ma, it's because…

167
00:12:55,357 --> 00:12:57,026
Ma'am, I'm sorry.

168
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:59,111
It's my fault.

169
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,029
I'm sorry.

170
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:03,157
Baby, I'm sorry.

171
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,700
Uncle is just excited.

172
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:05,618
You're okay, right?

173
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,502
How about you? What are you doing here?

174
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:18,881
We have new evidence that points
to a new suspect.

175
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:20,299
We need to talk to that person.

176
00:13:20,716 --> 00:13:21,967
There's a new suspect?

177
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:28,641
Sam,

178
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:31,227
is it you?

179
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:32,520
It's not her.

180
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:37,316
If it's not Sam, who is it?

181
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:41,570
Mr. Francis Castillo.

182
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:02,508
Sarge, my brother is innocent.

183
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:04,677
He had no reason to kill Basil.

184
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:05,803
Sam!

185
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:07,596
Sam, please take it easy.

186
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,515
- Sam!
- Hold on.

187
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,100
- Sam, please.
- I'm sorry.

188
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:12,726
- I'm sorry but you have to stay here.
- Okay.

189
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:14,436
Don't stress my grandchild.

190
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,398
Sit here for now. Let's wait here.

191
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:18,649
Sit down.

192
00:14:21,318 --> 00:14:22,444
Sit down.

193
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,573
Just calm down, Sam.

194
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:26,532
Calm down.

195
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:28,409
- Your brother is innocent.
- Here, give me that.

196
00:14:28,492 --> 00:14:29,785
Thank you, Amando.

197
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:30,911
Here.

198
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:32,496
Drink some water.

199
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,274
Why are the press here?

200
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:02,526
I ordered a news blackout.

201
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:05,905
Okay, sir. I'll call the PR Department.

202
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:06,989
Never mind.

203
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,170
Mr. Palacios, is it true
that your son was poisoned?

204
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:22,588
Is this similar to what happened

205
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:23,672
to Mr. Paco Palacios?

206
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:24,924
Was it an accident too?

207
00:15:25,007 --> 00:15:27,468
Any comments, sir,
on the two deaths in the family?

208
00:15:27,801 --> 00:15:29,428
Mr. Galvan, do you already have a suspect?

209
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:34,767
I'm requesting all of you to be patient.

210
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:37,770
Once the investigation is done,

211
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,230
you'll get your answers.

212
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,024
I will call for a press conference

213
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:47,446
but for now, please respect my request.

214
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:49,782
- Any information, sir?
- Confirmation, sir!

215
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:51,700
- Later. Later, please.
- Any information, sir?

216
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:53,994
- Later, please.
- Sir Galvan--

217
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:19,019
Sarge, why am I a suspect?

218
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:21,105
I have nothing to do with Basil's death.

219
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:34,284
Someone reported to us that
you fought with Mr. Palacios.

220
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:36,286
It was caught on CCTV.

221
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:45,045
3K? Are you jerks?

222
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:46,422
My brother-in-law's jacket is branded.

223
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,465
If that's the case,
I'll just sell it to someone else.

224
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:49,967
You fool!

225
00:16:52,302 --> 00:16:54,638
You are selling Paco's things?

226
00:16:57,224 --> 00:16:59,518
Does Auntie Aurora know about this?

227
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:08,861
<i>Hey, peasant.</i>

228
00:17:08,944 --> 00:17:10,654
<i>How dare you walk away from me?</i>

229
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:15,492
Don't report me to Ma'am Aurora, please.

230
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:18,579
Not only Auntie Aurora.

231
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:22,708
I will tell everyone at this party
that a thief is living here.

232
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:24,293
Especially your sister.

233
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:25,919
I am not a thief!

234
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:27,129
I'm not!

235
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:29,256
Stupid!

236
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:30,674
You're so stupid!

237
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:32,176
What do you call what you were doing?

238
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:41,769
Stay down, lowlife!

239
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:47,816
Francis! Francis, don't!

240
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,907
You know, you look good together.

241
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:02,623
Two losers in one frame.

242
00:18:11,965 --> 00:18:13,425
That's enough.

243
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,866
Sir, I had no…

244
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:41,453
I had no plans of hitting him
with that shovel.

245
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:43,747
I was just trying to scare him.

246
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:48,293
Mr. Castillo, how do you explain this?

247
00:18:50,045 --> 00:18:54,758
Your fingerprints are
on Mr. Palacios' wine glass.

248
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:02,975
Yes, sir, that's right.

249
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:07,855
The reason I touched his glass
was because after we fought,

250
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,816
I got scared
that he might really report me.

251
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:12,568
<i>I was nervous because…</i>

252
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:15,571
<i>I was sure I'd be in trouble with Sam</i>

253
00:19:15,654 --> 00:19:18,907
<i>once she found out</i>
<i>that I was selling Paco's jackets.</i>

254
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:22,452
<i>I went looking for Basil. I was restless.</i>

255
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:24,204
<i>So to calm my nerves…</i>

256
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,415
Hey, why are you drinking that?

257
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:28,333
That's Sir Basil's!

258
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,544
I'm sorry.

259
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:34,381
- I was just trying to calm myself. Sorry.
- There are a lot of drinks at the bar.

260
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:36,008
Just get one over there.

261
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,685
Sir, I touched it accidentally.

262
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:50,230
Please believe me. You can even ask Peter.

263
00:19:50,314 --> 00:19:51,732
Believe me.

264
00:19:51,815 --> 00:19:52,941
He knows.

265
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:07,164
Sam…

266
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:09,958
My child, calm down.

267
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:12,461
Your brother is innocent.

268
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:30,520
The staff that we talked to

269
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:34,316
said that you have lung cancer.

270
00:20:34,399 --> 00:20:35,484
Is that right?

271
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,860
Yes, sir.

272
